  "prompt": "What are the best recipes for small batch chocolate chip cookies?",
  "response": "Sure! Here's a great small batch chocolate chip cookie recipe that yields about a dozen cookies:\n\n### Small Batch Chocolate Chip Cookies\n\n#### Ingredients:\n- **1/4 cup (57g) unsalted butter**, softened\n- **1/4 cup (50g) granulated sugar**\n- **1/4 cup (50g) brown sugar**, packed\n- **1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract**\n- **1/4 teaspoon salt**\n- **1/2 teaspoon baking soda**\n- **1 egg yolk** (from a large egg)\n- **3/4 cup (95g) all-purpose flour**\n- **1/2 cup (90g) chocolate chips** (or chunks)\n\n#### Instructions:\n1. **Preheat oven** to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper or a silicone baking mat.\n2. **Cream butter and sugars** together in a medium-sized bowl until smooth and creamy.\n3. **Add vanilla extract, salt, and baking soda** to the mixture and combine well.\n4. **Mix in egg yolk** until fully incorporated.\n5. **Gradually add flour**, mixing until just combined. Do not overmix.\n6. **Fold in chocolate chips** or chunks evenly throughout the dough.\n7. **Scoop dough** with a tablespoon or cookie scoop and place on the prepared baking sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart.\n8. **Bake for 9-11 minutes**, or until the edges are lightly golden but the centers are still soft.\n9. **Cool on the baking sheet** for 5 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\n### Tips:\n- **Butter and sugars:** Make sure the butter is softened but not melted for the best texture.\n- **Egg yolk:** Using just the yolk ensures the cookies are tender and chewy.\n- **Chilling dough:** If you have time, chill the dough for 30 minutes to enhance the flavor and texture.\n- **Doneness:** Cookies will continue to cook slightly after being removed from the oven, so it's okay if they look a bit underdone in the center.\n\nEnjoy your freshly baked small batch chocolate chip cookies!",
